HatValidator_onInstall
├── when caller has already installed
│   └── it should revert with AlreadyInstalled
└── when caller has not installed
    ├── it should store the hats address keyed by msg.sender
    ├── it should store the hatId keyed by msg.sender
    └── it should emit HatValidatorInstalled

HatValidator_onUninstall
├── when caller has not installed
│   └── it should revert with NotInstalled
└── when caller has installed
    ├── it should clear the config for msg.sender
    └── it should emit HatValidatorUninstalled

HatValidator_isModuleType
├── given typeID is 1 (validator)
│   └── it should return true
└── given typeID is not 1
    └── it should return false

HatValidator_isAuthorized
├── given account has no config (not installed)
│   └── it should return false
└── given account has a config
    ├── when caller wears the hat
    │   └── it should return true
    └── when caller does not wear the hat
        └── it should return false

HatValidator_validateUserOp
├── given account has no config
│   └── it should return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED
└── given account has a config
    ├── when EOA recovered signer wears the hat
    │   └── it should return 0 (success)
    ├── when EOA recovered signer does not wear the hat
    │   ├── when contract signer wears hat and returns valid magic value
    │   │   └── it should return 0 (success)
    │   ├── when contract signer does not wear hat
    │   │   └── it should return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED
    │   ├── when contract signer returns invalid magic value
    │   │   └── it should return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED
    │   ├── when signer address is not a contract (EOA)
    │   │   └── it should return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED
    │   └── when signature is too short to contain an address
    │       └── it should return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED
    └── when neither EOA nor contract signer is valid
        └── it should return SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED

HatValidator_isValidSignatureWithSender
├── given account has no config
│   └── it should return 0xffffffff (failure)
└── given account has a config
    ├── when EOA recovered signer wears the hat
    │   └── it should return 0x1626ba7e (ERC-1271 magic value)
    ├── when EOA recovered signer does not wear the hat
    │   ├── when contract signer wears hat and returns valid magic value
    │   │   └── it should return 0x1626ba7e (ERC-1271 magic value)
    │   ├── when contract signer does not wear hat
    │   │   └── it should return 0xffffffff (failure)
    │   ├── when contract signer returns invalid magic value
    │   │   └── it should return 0xffffffff (failure)
    │   ├── when signer address is not a contract (EOA)
    │   │   └── it should return 0xffffffff (failure)
    │   └── when signature is too short to contain an address
    │       └── it should return 0xffffffff (failure)
    └── when neither EOA nor contract signer is valid
        └── it should return 0xffffffff (failure)

HatValidator_hats
├── given account has no config
│   └── it should return address(0)
└── given account has a config
    └── it should return the configured hats address

HatValidator_hatId
├── given account has no config
│   └── it should return 0
└── given account has a config
    └── it should return the configured hat ID

HatValidator_isInstalledOn
├── given account has not called onInstall
│   └── it should return false
└── given account has called onInstall
    └── it should return true
